Magenta RealTime (architecture and upstream weights)
================================================================================

StyleStreamer is built on the Magenta RealTime model stack
(SpectroStream audio codec, MusicCoCa style model, and Depthformer LLM),
originally developed by Google DeepMind and published at:

    https://github.com/magenta/magenta-realtime

Copyright 2025 Google LLC
Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

The C++ MLX runtime (vendor/magenta-realtime-mlx-cpp) is a derivative work
of the Magenta RealTime architecture, reimplemented in C++ and MLX by
Brian Cruz, and is also licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
See vendor/magenta-realtime-mlx-cpp/NOTICE for the full upstream attribution.

Model weights distributed via the Hugging Face dataset
    https://huggingface.co/datasets/rhymeswithlion/magenta-realtime-mlx-cpp
are derivative works of the upstream Magenta RealTime weights and are
licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License
(CC-BY 4.0), Copyright 2025 Google LLC. Use of those weights is also
subject to Google's Magenta RealTime Terms of Use, reproduced in the
dataset README.

The MusicCoCa encoder in that bundle (musiccoca_encoder.safetensors) has
been lightly fine-tuned by Brian Cruz to better match the outputs of the
original XLA SavedModel. The fine-tune deltas are licensed under
Apache 2.0, Copyright 2026 Brian Cruz; the underlying upstream encoder
weights remain under CC-BY 4.0 as stated above.

